title: For Sale:  Rare SAR-1 AK (AKM, AK-47) with extras
postcontent: I have for sale a Romanian SAR-1, an AK variant, also known as an AKM or AK-47. It was imported from Romania by Century. It is all numbers matching, with a scope mount and chrome lined barrel. It was manufactured by ROMARM / Cugir, which is a state owned defense company that is one of the oldest defense companies of Romania, with history dating back to the year 1799, long before the Russians invented the AK. The rifle is in good condition, with some scratches and wear to the original Romanian factory finish. This is NOT a Century US made weapon, and NOT a WASR, the more common Romanian import. This weapon is more rare, and features magazine dimples on the receiver, indicative of the fact that this was designed for real double stack mags and not carved out and modified for them like a WASR. It functions flawlessly and everything looks straight. The only issue I had was some trigger slap, which I fixed by having an upgraded Texas AK trigger professionally installed by Kilo Guns.This rifle will be solid as pictured, cleaned up and good to go right out of the box, with the following included:Authentic collectable Romanian military sling, magazine pouch, oil bottle and cleaning kitOriginal Romanian steel magazineThree Tapco polymer magazinesI bought this item new from a dealer / collector, and put less than a few hundred rounds through it, which for an AK is miniscule.
